        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 4:33PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 433 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gold Hill, or near Dillwyn, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
New Canton...
and Gold Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
